cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a power management scheme that optimizes the real power consumption and reactive power outputs of PV inverters in distribution networks. This involves controlling the power flow and voltage levels in the network, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper formulates a convex stochastic program to optimize the power flow in the network, which involves modeling uncertain real power injections as random variables. This can be seen as an application of AI techniques to power system optimization.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a decentralized algorithm for finding the global optimum point in the stochastic program, which is suitable for implementation in distribution networks with a large number of scenarios. This involves distributing the computation across multiple nodes in the network, which falls under the domain of distributed computing.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with power management in distribution networks, which involves the interaction of multiple devices and nodes in the network. This can be seen as an application of networking and internet architecture principles to power system optimization.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes an algorithm for optimizing power flow in distribution networks, which involves developing software to implement the algorithm. This can be seen as an application of software engineering principles to power system optimization.
